#https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3569933/is-it-possible-to-define-more-than-one-function-per-file-in-matlab-and-access-t#The only way to have multiple, separately accessible functions in a single file is to define STATIC METHODS using object-oriented programming. You'd access the function as myClass.static1(), myClass.static2() etc.function bool=allTrue(varargin)  bool=true;  for i=1:length(varargin)    if(all(all(varargin{i}))==0)    bool=false;    break;  endifendfor
endfunction
